cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about human parsing, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a novel neural network architecture, which involves designing attention routing and semantic aggregation modules, indicating that it may also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper uses multiple datasets and conducts experiments, suggesting that it may also fall under cs.MM (Multimedia) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
